{#-
  ============================================================================
  CALIFORNIA ASSOCIATION OF REALTORS® — Residential Lease or
  Month-to-Month Rental Agreement (LR-11) — Jinja2 / HTML template
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Structural features intentionally reproduced (chunker test cases):
    - CAR-style header with logo and form number; per-page footer boilerplate
    - 42 numbered clauses mirroring LR-11 order; short clauses alongside long
    - Nested sub-clauses A./B./C./D. and inline conditionals
    - Checkbox "Check A or B" patterns (term type, parking, storage, condition)
    - Checkbox-gated clauses (lead paint §22, military ordinance §34, HOA §15)
    - Fill-in-the-blank underline fields (empty ⇒ ruled line via fill() macro)
    - Move-in costs table (§5) with Category / Total Due / Received / Balance
    - Keys receipt sub-table (§18)
    - Signature block with multi-tenant and dual-broker rows
    - Cross-references to other paragraphs ("as specified in paragraph 2A")
  ============================================================================
-#}

{#- ---------- macros ---------- -#}
{%- macro fill(value, width='180px') -%}
  {%- set width_class = 'field-w-' ~ (width | replace('px', '')) -%}
  {%- if value is not none and value|string|trim != '' -%}
    <span class="field filled {{ width_class }}">{{ value }}</span>
  {%- else -%}
    <span class="field blank {{ width_class }}">&nbsp;</span>
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- macro box(checked) -%}
  <span class="cb">{{ '☒' if (checked is defined and checked) else '☐' }}</span>
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- set L = lease | default({}) -%}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<style>
  @page {
    size: Letter;
    margin: 50px 54px 64px 54px;
    @bottom-left  { content: "CALIFORNIA RESIDENTIAL LEASE OR MONTH-TO-MONTH RENTAL AGREEMENT  (LR-11 Rev. 10/01)"; font-size: 6.8pt; color:#555; }
    @bottom-center{ content: "Premises: {{ L.property_address | default('________________') }}"; font-size: 6.8pt; color:#555; }
    @bottom-right { content: "Page " counter(page) " of " counter(pages); font-size: 6.8pt; color:#555; }
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    font-family: "Times New Roman", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 8.8pt;
    line-height: 1.32;
    color: #111;
  }

  /* ---------- header ---------- */
  .masthead { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; padding-bottom: 4px; }
  .logo-block { flex: 0 0 68px; }
  .logo-box {
    width: 64px; height: 64px;
    border: 2px solid #1a3a5c; border-radius: 4px;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    color: #1a3a5c; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: bold;
    font-family: Georgia, serif; letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    line-height: 1.3; text-align: center;
  }
  .masthead .title-block { flex: 1; text-align: center; padding-top: 6px; }
  .doc-title { font-weight: bold; font-size: 13pt; letter-spacing: .3px; line-height: 1.3; }
  .doc-sub   { font-size: 7.5pt; color:#333; }
  .rule { border: none; border-top: 2px solid #1a3a5c; margin: 4px 0 8px 0; }
  .rule-thin { border:none; border-top:1px solid #999; margin: 7px 0; }

  /* ---------- preamble ---------- */
  .preamble { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .preamble-parties { display: flex; gap: 6px; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .preamble-parties .label { white-space: nowrap; font-style: normal; }
  .party-line { border-bottom: 1px solid #222; flex: 1; display: inline-block; min-width: 200px; padding: 0 4px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; color:#13335c; }

  /* ---------- clauses ---------- */
  .clause { margin: 0 0 5px 0; text-align: justify; }
  .clause > .num { font-weight: bold; }
  .clause-title { font-weight: bold; }
  .sub  { margin: 2px 0 2px 18px; text-align: justify; }
  .subsub { margin: 2px 0 2px 36px; text-align: justify; }
  .sublabel { font-weight: bold; }

  /* ---------- fill-in fields & checkboxes ---------- */
  .field {
    display: inline-block;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #222;
    padding: 0 3px;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }
  .field.filled { font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; color:#13335c; }
  .field-w-40  { min-width: 40px; }
  .field-w-50  { min-width: 50px; }
  .field-w-70  { min-width: 70px; }
  .field-w-90  { min-width: 90px; }
  .field-w-100 { min-width: 100px; }
  .field-w-110 { min-width: 110px; }
  .field-w-120 { min-width: 120px; }
  .field-w-140 { min-width: 140px; }
  .field-w-150 { min-width: 150px; }
  .field-w-160 { min-width: 160px; }
  .field-w-180 { min-width: 180px; }
  .field-w-200 { min-width: 200px; }
  .field-w-210 { min-width: 210px; }
  .field-w-230 { min-width: 230px; }
  .field-w-260 { min-width: 260px; }
  .field-w-280 { min-width: 280px; }
  .field-w-300 { min-width: 300px; }
  .field-w-320 { min-width: 320px; }
  .field-w-340 { min-width: 340px; }
  .field-w-380 { min-width: 380px; }
  .cb { font-size: 10.5pt; vertical-align: -1px; padding-right: 2px; }

  /* ---------- initials line ---------- */
  .initials {
    margin-top: 8px; padding-top: 3px; border-top: 1px solid #bbb;
    font-size: 7.8pt; color:#333; display:flex; justify-content: space-between;
  }

  /* ---------- tables ---------- */
  table.grid { width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 3px 0 5px 0; font-size: 8pt; }
  table.grid th, table.grid td { border: 1px solid #555; padding: 2px 4px; text-align:left; }
  table.grid th { background:#eef2f6; font-weight:bold; }

  /* ---------- signature block ---------- */
  .sig-block { margin-top: 10px; }
  .sig-line { display:flex; gap:20px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .sig-cell { flex: 1; border-bottom: 1px solid #333; padding-bottom: 1px; font-size: 8pt; }
  .sig-label { font-size: 7.5pt; color:#444; }
  .notice-box { border:1px solid #555; padding:5px 8px; margin:5px 0; background:#fbfbf5; font-size: 8pt; }
  .small { font-size: 7.4pt; color:#444; }
  .page-break { break-before: page; }
  .bold { font-weight: bold; }
  .equal-housing { float:right; font-size:7pt; border:1px solid #333; padding:2px 4px; margin-left:6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

{#- ============================ PAGE 1 ============================ -#}
<div class="masthead">
  <div class="logo-block">
    <div class="logo-box">CALIFORNIA<br>ASSOCIATION<br>OF<br>REALTORS®</div>
  </div>
  <div class="title-block">
    <div class="doc-title">RESIDENTIAL LEASE OR<br>MONTH-TO-MONTH RENTAL AGREEMENT</div>
    <div class="doc-sub">LR-11 REVISED DATE 10/01</div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="rule">

<div class="preamble">
  <div class="preamble-parties">
    {{ fill(L.landlord_name, '260px') }} <span class="label">(&ldquo;Landlord&rdquo;) and</span>
  </div>
  <div class="preamble-parties">
    {{ fill(L.tenant_name, '260px') }} <span class="label">(&ldquo;Tenant&rdquo;) agree as follows:</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">1.</span> <span class="clause-title">PROPERTY:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Landlord rents to Tenant and Tenant rents from Landlord, the real property and improvements described as:
    {{ fill(L.property_address, '340px') }} (&ldquo;Premises&rdquo;).
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> The following personal property is included:
    {{ fill(L.included_property, '340px') }}.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">2.</span> <span class="clause-title">TERM:</span>
  The term begins on (date) {{ fill(L.start_date, '140px') }} (&ldquo;Commencement Date&rdquo;),
  <span class="sublabel">(Check A or B):</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.term_is_month_to_month) }} <span class="sublabel">A. Month-to-month:</span>
    and continues as a month-to-month tenancy. Either party may terminate the tenancy by giving written notice
    to the other at least 30 days prior to the intended termination date, subject to any applicable local laws.
    Such notice may be given on any date.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.term_is_fixed) }} <span class="sublabel">B. Lease:</span>
    and shall terminate on (date) {{ fill(L.end_date, '140px') }} at
    {{ box(L.end_time_am) }} AM &nbsp; {{ box(L.end_time_pm) }} PM.
    Any holding over after the term of this Agreement expires, with Landlord&rsquo;s consent, shall create a
    month-to-month tenancy which either party may terminate as specified in paragraph 2A. Rent shall be at a
    rate equal to the rent for the immediately preceding month, unless otherwise notified by Landlord, payable
    in advance. All other terms and conditions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">3.</span> <span class="clause-title">RENT:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant agrees to pay rent at the rate of {{ fill(L.rent_amount, '110px') }}
    per month for the term of the Agreement.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Rent is payable in advance on the
    <span class="bold">1st</span> (or {{ fill(L.rent_due_day, '40px') }}) day of each calendar month,
    and is delinquent on the next day.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> If Commencement Date falls on any day other than the first day of the month,
    rent shall be prorated based on a 30-day period. If Tenant has paid one full month&rsquo;s rent in advance
    of Commencement Date, rent for the second calendar month shall be prorated based on a 30-day period.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">D.</span> PAYMENT: The rent shall be paid by
    {{ box(L.pay_cash) }} cash,
    {{ box(L.pay_check) }} personal check,
    {{ box(L.pay_money_order) }} money order,
    {{ box(L.pay_cashier_check) }} cashier check,
    {{ box(L.pay_other) }} other {{ fill(L.pay_other_desc, '120px') }},
    to (name) {{ fill(L.payee_name, '160px') }} &nbsp; (phone) {{ fill(L.payee_phone, '120px') }} at
    (address) {{ fill(L.payee_address, '260px') }},
    (or at any other location specified by Landlord in writing to Tenant) between the hours of
    {{ fill(L.payment_hours_start, '90px') }} and {{ fill(L.payment_hours_end, '90px') }}
    on the following days {{ fill(L.payment_days, '180px') }}.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">4.</span> <span class="clause-title">SECURITY DEPOSIT:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant agrees to pay {{ fill(L.deposit_amount, '110px') }} as a security
    deposit. Security deposit will be {{ box(L.deposit_held_by_owner) }} transferred to and held by the Owner
    of the Premises; or {{ box(L.deposit_held_by_broker) }} held in Owner&rsquo;s Broker&rsquo;s trust account.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> All or any portion of the security deposit may be used, as reasonably
    necessary, to: (1) cure Tenant&rsquo;s default in payment of rent, Late Charges, non-sufficient funds
    (&ldquo;NSF&rdquo;) fees, or other sums due; (2) repair damage, excluding ordinary wear and tear, caused
    by Tenant or by a guest or licensee of Tenant; (3) clean Premises, if necessary, upon termination of
    tenancy; and (4) replace or return personal property or appurtenances.
    <span class="bold">SECURITY DEPOSIT SHALL NOT BE USED BY TENANT IN LIEU OF PAYMENT OF LAST MONTH&rsquo;S RENT.</span>
    If all or any portion of the security deposit is used during tenancy, Tenant agrees to reinstate the total
    security deposit within five days after written notice is delivered to Tenant. Within three weeks after Tenant
    vacates the Premises, Landlord shall: (1) furnish Tenant an itemized statement indicating the amount of any
    security deposit received and the basis for its disposition; and (2) return any remaining portion of security
    deposit to Tenant.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> No interest will be paid on security deposit unless required by local ordinance.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">D.</span> If security deposit is held by Owner, Tenant agrees not to hold Broker
    responsible for its return. If security deposit is held in Owner&rsquo;s Broker&rsquo;s trust account, and
    Broker&rsquo;s authority is terminated before expiration of this Agreement, and security deposits are
    released to someone other than Tenant, then Broker shall notify Tenant, in writing, where and to whom
    security deposit has been released. Once Tenant has been provided such notice, Tenant agrees not to hold
    Broker responsible for security deposit.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">5.</span> <span class="clause-title">MOVE-IN COSTS RECEIVED/DUE:</span>
  <table class="grid">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style="width:38%">Category</th>
        <th style="width:16%">Total Due</th>
        <th style="width:18%">Payment Received</th>
        <th style="width:14%">Balance Due</th>
        <th style="width:14%">Date Due</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in L.move_in_rows | default([]) %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ row.category }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.total_due }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.payment_received }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.balance_due }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.date_due }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% else %}
      <tr><td>Rent from &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; to &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (date)</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>*Security Deposit</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Other</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <div class="small">*The maximum amount that Landlord may receive as security deposit, however designated, cannot
  exceed two month&rsquo;s rent for an unfurnished Premises, or three month&rsquo;s rent for a furnished premises.</div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">6.</span> <span class="clause-title">PARKING: (Check A or B)</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.parking_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Parking is permitted as follows:
    {{ fill(L.parking_description, '280px') }}.
    The right to parking is, {{ box(L.parking_included_in_rent) }} is,
    {{ box(L.parking_not_included_in_rent) }} is not, included in the rent charged pursuant to paragraph 3.
    If not included in the rent, the parking rental fee shall be an additional
    {{ fill(L.parking_fee, '80px') }} per month. Parking space(s) are to be used for parking operable motor
    vehicles, except for trailers, boats, campers, buses or trucks (other than pick-up trucks). Tenant shall
    park in assigned space(s) only. Parking space(s) are to be kept clean. Vehicles leaking oil, gas or other
    motor vehicle fluids shall not be parked on the Premises. Mechanical work or storage of inoperable vehicles
    is not allowed in parking space(s) or elsewhere on the Premises.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    OR &nbsp; {{ box(L.parking_not_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">B.</span>
    Parking is not permitted on the Premises.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="initials">
  <span>Landlord&rsquo;s Initials ( {{ L.landlord_initials | default('______') }} ) ( {{ L.landlord_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
  <span>Tenant&rsquo;s Initials ( {{ L.tenant_initials | default('______') }} ) ( {{ L.tenant_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
</div>

{#- ============================ PAGE 2 ============================ -#}
<div class="page-break"></div>

<div class="clause" style="margin-top:4px;">
  <span class="num">7.</span> <span class="clause-title">STORAGE: (Check A or B)</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.storage_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Storage is permitted as follows:
    {{ fill(L.storage_description, '260px') }}.
    The right to storage space is, {{ box(L.storage_included_in_rent) }} is,
    {{ box(L.storage_not_included_in_rent) }} is not, included in the rent charged pursuant to paragraph 3.
    If not included in rent, storage space shall be an additional {{ fill(L.storage_fee, '80px') }} per month.
    Tenant shall store only personal property that Tenant owns, and shall not store property that is claimed by
    another or in which another has any right, title, or interest. Tenant shall not store any improperly packaged
    food or perishable goods, flammable materials, explosives, or other inherently dangerous material.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    OR &nbsp; {{ box(L.storage_not_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">B.</span>
    Storage is not permitted on the Premises.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">8.</span> <span class="clause-title">LATE CHARGE/NSF CHECKS:</span>
  Tenant acknowledges that either late payment of rent or issuance of a NSF check may cause Landlord to incur
  costs and expenses, the exact amount of which are extremely difficult and impractical to determine. These costs
  may include, but are not limited to, processing, enforcement and accounting expenses, and late charges imposed
  on Landlord. If any installment of rent due from Tenant is not received by Landlord within
  <span class="bold">{{ fill(L.late_grace_days, '30px') }} calendar days</span> after date due, or if a check
  is returned NSF, Tenant shall pay to Landlord, respectively, an additional sum of
  {{ fill(L.late_charge_amount, '90px') }} as Late Charge and {{ fill(L.nsf_fee, '70px') }} as a NSF fee,
  either or both of which shall be deemed additional rent. Landlord and Tenant agree that these charges represent
  a fair and reasonable estimate of the costs Landlord may incur by reason of Tenant&rsquo;s late or NSF payment.
  Any Late Charge or NSF fee due shall be paid with the current installment of rent. Landlord&rsquo;s acceptance
  of any Late Charge or NSF fee shall not constitute a waiver as to any default of Tenant. Landlord&rsquo;s right
  to collect a Late Charge or NSF fee shall not be deemed an extension of the date rent is due under paragraph 3,
  or prevent Landlord from exercising any other rights and remedies under this Agreement, and as provided by law.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">9.</span> <span class="clause-title">CONDITION OF PREMISES:</span>
  Tenant has examined Premises, all furniture, furnishings, appliances, landscaping, if any, and fixtures,
  including smoke detector(s).
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">(Check one:)</span>
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.condition_option_a) }} <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant acknowledges that these items are
    clean and in operative condition, with the following exceptions
    {{ fill(L.condition_exceptions, '280px') }}.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    OR {{ box(L.condition_option_b) }} <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Tenant&rsquo;s acknowledgment of the
    condition of these items is contained in an attached statement of condition (such as C.A.R.&rsquo;s MIMO-11).
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    OR {{ box(L.condition_option_c) }} <span class="sublabel">C.</span> Tenant will provide Landlord a list of
    items that are damaged or not in operable condition within
    {{ fill(L.condition_inspection_days, '30px') }} days after Commencement Date, not as a contingency of this
    Agreement but rather as an acknowledgment of the condition of the Premises.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    OR {{ box(L.condition_option_d) }} <span class="sublabel">D.</span> Other:
    {{ fill(L.condition_other_desc, '260px') }}.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">10.</span> <span class="clause-title">NEIGHBORHOOD CONDITIONS:</span>
  Tenant is advised to satisfy him or herself as to neighborhood or area conditions, including schools, proximity
  and adequacy of law enforcement, crime statistics, registered felons or offenders, fire protection, other
  governmental services, proximity to commercial, industrial or agricultural activities, existing and proposed
  transportation, construction and development that may affect noise, view, or traffic, airport noise, noise or
  odor from any source, wild and domestic animals, other nuisances, hazards, or circumstances, facilities and
  condition of common areas, conditions and influences of significance to certain cultures and/or religions, and
  personal needs, requirements and preferences of Tenant.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">11.</span> <span class="clause-title">UTILITIES:</span>
  Tenant agrees to pay for all utilities and services, and the following charges:
  {{ fill(L.utilities_additional, '200px') }}
  except {{ fill(L.landlord_pays_utilities, '200px') }}, which shall be paid for by Landlord. If any utilities
  are not separately metered, Tenant shall pay Tenant&rsquo;s proportional share, as reasonably determined by Landlord.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">12.</span> <span class="clause-title">OCCUPANTS:</span>
  The Premises are for the sole use as a personal residence by the following named persons only:
  {{ fill(L.occupants_list, '320px') }}.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">13.</span> <span class="clause-title">PETS:</span>
  No animal or pet shall be kept on or about the Premises without Landlord&rsquo;s prior written consent, except
  {{ fill(L.pets_exception, '260px') }}.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">14.</span> <span class="clause-title">RULES/REGULATIONS:</span>
  Tenant agrees to comply with all rules and regulations of Landlord, which are at any time posted on the Premises
  or delivered to Tenant. Tenant shall not, and shall ensure that guests and licensees of Tenant shall not,
  disturb, annoy, endanger, or interfere with other tenants of the building or neighbors, or use the Premises for
  any unlawful purposes, including, but not limited to, using, manufacturing, selling, storing, or transporting
  illicit drugs or other contraband, or violate any law or ordinance, or commit a waste or nuisance on or about
  the Premises.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">15.</span> <span class="clause-title">CONDOMINIUM/PLANNED UNIT DEVELOPMENT:</span>
  {{ box(L.is_hoa) }} (If checked) The Premises is a unit in a condominium, planned unit, or other development
  governed by a homeowners&rsquo; association (&ldquo;HOA&rdquo;). The name of the HOA is
  {{ fill(L.hoa_name, '200px') }}.
  Tenant agrees to comply with all covenants, conditions and restrictions, bylaws, rules and regulations and
  decisions of HOA. Landlord shall provide Tenant copies of rules and regulations, if any. Tenant shall reimburse
  Landlord for any fines or charges imposed by HOA or other authorities, due to any violation by Tenant, or the
  guests or licensees of Tenant.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">16.</span> <span class="clause-title">MAINTENANCE:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant shall properly use, operate and safeguard Premises, including if
    applicable, any landscaping, furniture, furnishings, and appliances, and all mechanical, electrical, gas and
    plumbing fixtures, and keep them clean and sanitary. Tenant shall immediately notify Landlord, in writing, of
    any problem, malfunction or damage. Tenant shall pay for all repairs or replacements caused by Tenant, or
    guests of Tenant, excluding ordinary wear and tear. Tenant shall pay for all damage to Premises as a result
    of failure to report a problem in a timely manner. Tenant shall pay for repair of drain blockages or stoppages,
    unless caused by defective plumbing parts or tree roots invading sewer lines.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span>
    {{ box(L.water_landlord) }} Landlord &nbsp; {{ box(L.water_tenant) }} Tenant shall water the garden,
    landscaping, trees and shrubs, except {{ fill(L.watering_exceptions, '200px') }}.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span>
    {{ box(L.maint_landlord) }} Landlord &nbsp; {{ box(L.maint_tenant) }} Tenant shall maintain the garden,
    landscaping, trees and shrubs, except {{ fill(L.maintenance_exceptions, '200px') }}.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">17.</span> <span class="clause-title">ALTERATIONS:</span>
